"{\"uid\": \"sbs.com.au-news-article-paris-olympics-day-six-women-continue-to-bring-in-the-medals-for-australia-q3nvdbd5q\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Stream free online, anytime  Discover your world of SBS  Sign in or create an account  or  Stream free online, anytime  Get in touch:  Highlights around SBS:  Follow Us:  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lani Pallister, Bri Throssell, Ariarne Titmus and Mollie O'Callaghan won the Womens 4 x 200m Freestyle Relay Finals.Source:AAP/DAVE HUNT  It would not be an understatement to say that the women's teams are carrying the load for Australia at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 357, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mollie O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The majority of Australia's medals have been won by female athletes, including all of the gold in the tally so far.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sixth day of the Olympic Games may not have seen a great number of medals added to the Australian total (just two), but it did generate promise for more success in the coming days.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9488564696569982, \"rank\": 0.05389988193801574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's group sports athletes enjoyed wins across the board, seeing them through to the next rounds of their competitions.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia remains fourth in the Paris Olympics table, standing only behind China, the USA, and hosts France.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8837813228179453, \"rank\": 0.13149255947798882, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.992270674727994, \"rank\": 0.004851219420001862, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The green and gold currently have 18, with eight gold, six silver and four bronze.\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team of Mollie O'Callaghan, Ariarne Titmus, Lani Pallister and Brianna Throssell have done it again - and in spectacular fashion - edging out their nearest opponents, the USA, by a whole 2.78 seconds to claim yet another gold medal.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1224, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mollie O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mollie_O'Callaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lani Pallister\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lani_Pallister\"}, {\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brianna_Throssell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brianna Throssell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brianna_Throssell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brianna_Throssell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At times, it appeared the Aussie swimmers were only competing with themselves, attempting to break their own world record.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, they were not able to achieve that, but Australian sports fans should be more than willing to forgive them for it.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9488564696569982, \"rank\": 0.05389988193801574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The success comes on the back of multiple other medals won by the Australian swim team, including a gold in the women's 100m backstroke and a silver in the men's 100m freestyle.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1768, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Swim_Team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian swim team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Swim_Team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Swim_Team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the blistering heat baking the streets of Paris, the 26-year-old from Victoria was able to dig deep and make it through the 20km race walk to finish in third.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.651315648690504e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9998753248156032, \"rank\": 0.00012449871595214724, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event was pushed back by almost half an hour, eventually starting at 9.50am (local time), with racers forced to compete under extreme circumstances.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At times things seemed hopeless for the Australian athlete, with China's Yang Jiayu and Spain's Maria Perez breaking away from the rest of the group early on, but she found what she needed to bounce back and claim her first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9488564696569982, \"rank\": 0.05389988193801574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2268, \"end\": 2273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8837813228179453, \"rank\": 0.13149255947798882, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\", \"score\": 0.9999925378334525, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Jiayu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Jiayu\"}, {\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999889225095662, \"rank\": 1.0747560254128894e-05, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"score\": 0.9692064644307549, \"rank\": 0.031762168016007356, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\"}, {\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\", \"score\": 0.9999998933976769, \"rank\": 8.683403453079445e-08, \"text\": \"Perez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Victorian said there were many times throughout the course of the event that she thought she would not even be able to complete the race, much less win a medal.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9997793680615351, \"rank\": 0.0002143355916781516, \"text\": \"Victorian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a day of dominance for the Australian teams at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2643, \"end\": 2653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9488564696569982, \"rank\": 0.05389988193801574, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In women's basketball, the Opals bounced back after their opening day loss to Nigeria, beating Canada 70-65, led by an impressive Sami Whitcomb who was on double figures (19 points, 10 assists.)\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.299551234064039e-27, \"text\": \"Opals\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2762, \"end\": 2769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8877853721836679, \"rank\": 0.12638309440174872, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2819, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Whitcomb\", \"score\": 0.9999999965707502, \"rank\": 2.888285343905713e-09, \"text\": \"Whitcomb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Whitcomb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Whitcomb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sandy Brondello's team will now face a tough challenge in their final match in the group by hosts France, but even a loss might see them through to the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2880, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sandy_Brondello\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sandy Brondello\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sandy_Brondello\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sandy_Brondello\"}, {\"begin\": 2978, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9528002207406833, \"rank\": 0.04837409994984566, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 3x3 basketball, the opening day results of one win and one loss by the Gangurrus could not have foretold what followed today.\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They started off by beating China 21-15, then went on to take out Tokyo gold-medallists USA, 17-15.\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3206, \"end\": 3211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8837813228179453, \"rank\": 0.13149255947798882, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8956877017650144, \"rank\": 0.11646056762669946, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3266, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.992270674727994, \"rank\": 0.004851219420001862, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are now set to face the hosts, but after these performances, it's hard to imagine anything being too difficult for them.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kookaburras also had a good day, bouncing back from their loss against Belgium by beating New Zealand 5-0.\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3405, \"end\": 3420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Kookaburras\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.989333949003621, \"rank\": 0.010207421704793086, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3499, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"score\": 0.7848396914638166, \"rank\": 0.2655256117279051, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The win seals Australia's place in the hockey quarter-finals, while the neighbours across the Tasman were sadly eliminated.\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99994656596729, \"rank\": 4.8779902056346125e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasman_Sea\", \"score\": 0.9999807105023668, \"rank\": 1.1831981857481847e-05, \"text\": \"Tasman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasman_Sea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasman_Sea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Hockeyroos also did well, despite not winning their match against Tokyo silver medallists Argentina.\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hockeyroos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8956877017650144, \"rank\": 0.11646056762669946, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3735, \"end\": 3744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.7837167540518591, \"rank\": 0.2227850274184705, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource